array() / [] – create array
count() – number of elements
sizeof() – alias of count()
is_array() – check if variable is array
in_array() – check if value exists

Adding / Removing Elements
array_push() – add to end
array_pop() – remove from end
array_shift() – remove from beginning
array_unshift() – add to beginning
unset() – remove specific element


Merging / Combining
array_merge() – merge arrays
array_merge_recursive()
array_combine() – combine keys + values
array_replace()

array_search() – find key by value
array_key_exists() – check if key exists


array_keys() – get all keys
array_values() – get all values
array_flip() – swap keys and values


array_filter() array_map() array_reduce()

array_slice() array_splice() array_chunk()

Array Difference & Comparison
array_diff() – values in A not in B
array_diff_assoc() – also checks keys
array_diff_key() – compare only keys
array_intersect() – common values
array_intersect_assoc()
array_intersect_key()


Walk / Callback Functions
For when you want to touch every element.
array_walk() – apply function to each element
array_walk_recursive() – for nested arrays

Useful for working with multi-dimensional arrays (like DB results).
array_column() – get one column from array

array_unique()
array_diff()
array_intersect()